# Next.js Demo Conventions

- API route handlers that touch SQLite or the engine must opt out of static
  optimization:

```ts
export const runtime = "nodejs";
export const dynamic = "force-dynamic";
```

- Native / Node-only packages (`better-sqlite3`, `node-cron`) are declared in
  `serverExternalPackages` in `next.config.ts`. Don't import them into client
  components.
- Server singletons (market engine, reporting state) live on `globalThis` so
  dev hot-reload doesn't spin up duplicates — follow that pattern for new ones.
- When building the dashboard, consume the existing API routes; do **not** edit
  files under `src/app/api/**` or `src/lib/server/**`.
